I was very disappointed to read in another review below that an individual with a service animal was asked to provide documentation by a staff member at this restaurant. I am a social worker, and this is 100% illegal and violates ADA law. Management, please train all of your staff to know that there are two questions and two questions only they can ask when approaching an individual with a service dog/animal: 1.) Is the dog or service animal required because of a disability? and 2.) What work or task has the dog been trained to perform? Asking for documentation or "proof" is, once again, illegal and violates ADA law. Please train your employees on this subject and do better to accommodate individuals with service dogs/animals.

Ordered from there on a Sunday. First, the food. Lots of flavor in the tacos. I had the Al Pastor and my wife had the steak. Al Pastor was very good, and the steak was super flavorful. The only knock, which I think is more personal preference based on how taquieras in my city do their tacos is that the steak could have been chopped a little finer and the meat had quite a few chewy bits in there. Could just be whatever cut of meat they use. Either way it was good. The horchata was some of the best I've had. A little heavier than Im used to but man was it good. I just wish we had to option of ordering more than a 12 oz serving for almost $4.00. My main reason for giving 3 stars is because our order was night right. I was missing a whole steak taco combo and my elote. I was able to call back and ask for a refund. The guy I spoke to was very nice and apologized, and said that we should have a refund for the missing items in a few days Don't let my missing items steer you away. Give them a try, but make sure you check your bag before leaving.

My accent (British) will have been a giveaway that I wasn’t a local and therefore was unlikely to have much of a clue about what was in each meal. As the coronavirus continues to batter businesses such as these, more of an effort should be made to encourage customers to return.
